## 🚫 DO NOT

- Use `any` type
- Skip error handling
- Hardcode project names/URLs/emails
- Forget RLS policies
- Use Stripe (use Razorpay)
- Skip awaiting params in Next.js 15
- Import server code in client components
- Forget to validate user input

---

## ✅ ALWAYS DO

- Import `brand` from `@/config/brand`
- Use `brand.name` for project references
- Enable RLS on all tables
- Validate with Zod
- Handle errors properly
- Use TypeScript types (no `any`)
- Await params in dynamic routes
- Check auth before logic

